1
00:00:01,370 --> 00:00:04,300
Huh? Ms. Horai?

2
00:00:05,140 --> 00:00:07,110
What's going on? Why is she here?

3
00:00:08,710 --> 00:00:10,480
Think.

4
00:00:11,210 --> 00:00:13,980
I, Nami Suzuki, came to Tokyo to work.

5
00:00:14,010 --> 00:00:18,120
My job is to do odd jobs for the
editor-in-chief of a fashion magazine.

6
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:18,920
But...

7
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:21,020
No conviction.

8
00:00:21,290 --> 00:00:23,120
Not even average perseverance.

9
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:25,760
I felt so low, I wanted to quit.

10
00:00:26,390 --> 00:00:29,060
Are dreams really that important?

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,300
What's the use
if dreams keep you from smiling?

12
00:00:32,630 --> 00:00:34,030
Be my girlfriend.

13
00:00:34,530 --> 00:00:36,100
- Girlfriend?
- For pretend.

14
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:38,570
And I'm supposed to meet his sister.

15
00:00:39,010 --> 00:00:41,110
But who arrived was...

16
00:00:42,340 --> 00:00:43,910
Oh, I see.

17
00:00:43,940 --> 00:00:45,780
No, I don't see!

18
00:00:45,810 --> 00:00:48,120
Calm down, Nami.

19
00:00:48,550 --> 00:00:54,350
Maybe I'm so stressed with Ms. Horai,
everyone I see looks like her now.

20
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:55,860
I'm Junnosuke's sister.

21
00:00:56,190 --> 00:00:57,290
Reiko Horai.

22
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:59,560
Nope, it's really her.

23
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,260
Ma'am.

24
00:01:02,630 --> 00:01:04,300
Hey, she's just my sister.

25
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:08,200
This is my girlfriend, Nami.

26
00:01:08,970 --> 00:01:10,900
I'm Suzuki.

27
00:01:10,940 --> 00:01:12,110
Nami.

28
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,710
Nami Suzuki?

29
00:01:15,740 --> 00:01:18,050
Yes, Ma'am.

30
00:01:20,010 --> 00:01:21,050
What's wrong?

31
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:23,880
I'm just surprised.

32
00:01:24,820 --> 00:01:28,320
That she's the girl
you wanted me to meet.

33
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:31,490
Wasn't the type I'd expected.

34
00:01:31,530 --> 00:01:32,430
Really?

35
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:34,760
Nami's actually a great cook.

36
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:38,130
I just follow recipes.
I have no originality whatsoever.

37
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,170
She's fluent in many languages.

38
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:43,740
I wish to be, and I've been thinking
about starting to study.

39
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:46,010
Anyways, she's a driven career woman.

40
00:01:46,610 --> 00:01:48,380
Oh, are you?

41
00:01:48,410 --> 00:01:51,680
- Yeah!
- I'm completely useless.

42
00:01:51,710 --> 00:01:54,580
Useless, incompetent,
so not career driven.

43
00:01:54,610 --> 00:01:57,850
Come on,
you told me how you loved to work.

44
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:59,850
That you wanted to work forever.

45
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:01,590
Did I?

46
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:03,920
She's like you that way.

47
00:02:04,390 --> 00:02:06,260
Your boss really relies on you, huh?

48
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:10,100
Not in the smallest bit,
not even a tiny morsel!

49
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:11,500
Huh, why?

50
00:02:11,530 --> 00:02:12,770
Didn't I tell you?

51
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,940
I work for Otowado now.

52
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:18,810
I'm your sister's odd job attendant.

53
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:21,940
What seriously? You mean that?

54
00:02:21,980 --> 00:02:25,950
Ms. Horai! I mean, Ms. Reiko...?

55
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:28,150
I'll go get something to drink.

56
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:30,380
Where's the sugar, Jun?

57
00:02:31,850 --> 00:02:32,990
Jun?

58
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:34,960
You should've told me.

59
00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:36,920
How was I supposed to know?

60
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:38,960
Your name is Horai?

61
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:41,960
Yeah. Junnosuke Horai.

62
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,330
- Didn't I say?
- No.

63
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:44,460
Yeah I did.

64
00:02:44,970 --> 00:02:47,430
You're a photographer?

65
00:02:47,470 --> 00:02:48,240
Yeah.

66
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:51,370
You like surfing and motorcycles.

67
00:02:51,410 --> 00:02:53,840
We started dating six months ago.

68
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:57,540
We met through mutual surfer friends.

69
00:02:57,580 --> 00:02:58,910
I don't surf.

70
00:02:58,950 --> 00:03:01,750
Neither do I. It's just a story.

71
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:05,950
Oh, what should I call you?

72
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,990
How about Jun?

73
00:03:09,460 --> 00:03:10,220
Jun.

74
00:03:11,690 --> 00:03:12,830
This is awkward.

75
00:03:13,290 --> 00:03:14,760
How about you?

76
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,960
Okay, you can call me Nami.

77
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:19,270
Nami.

78
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,070
Jun.

79
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:24,740
- Nami?
- Jun?

80
00:03:25,170 --> 00:03:25,970
Nami.

81
00:03:26,770 --> 00:03:29,140
- Jun.
- Nami...

82
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,680
I never said Horai, huh?

83
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:36,250
See? I would've noticed
if you'd have told me.

84
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:38,150
Should I tell her the truth then?

85
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,760
No, that would make it so awkward.

86
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:43,920
You're right.

87
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:45,490
What are you doing?

88
00:03:52,270 --> 00:03:53,030
Sis!

89
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:55,940
Stop it, Jun.

90
00:03:57,540 --> 00:03:58,310
So?

91
00:03:58,810 --> 00:03:59,670
Since when?

92
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:02,480
- Six months.
- One week.

93
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:06,150
- Six months.
- One week.

94
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:09,080
I thought...

95
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:12,390
She knows I only came to Tokyo
a week ago!

96
00:04:12,890 --> 00:04:13,820
Ouch!

97
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:15,960
Well, you see, um.

98
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:19,660
We met online through a mutual friend
six months ago.

99
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:22,130
That's right, online.

100
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:24,870
So it was long distance at first.

101
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,030
- But I wanted to be closer.
- So?

102
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:29,740
What do you like about him?

103
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:32,010
- The gap?
- I'm asking her.

104
00:04:32,610 --> 00:04:34,980
Um, well...

105
00:04:38,910 --> 00:04:42,120
The gap.
He's usually really laid back.

106
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,880
But sometimes, just sometimes.

107
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:48,320
He acts without thinking much
and, um, huh?

108
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:52,490
- We went to the sea the other day.
- Right.

109
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:54,860
And celebrated Kenchan's...

110
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:56,400
Ouch!

111
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:58,530
Kenchan?

112
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:03,100
Kenchan is, um...

113
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:08,610
Kenchan is...

114
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,280
I...

115
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:17,450
I'm a kendama champion.

116
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:18,750
Kendama?

117
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:20,590
- Champion?
- Yes.

118
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:22,790
Kendama champion. "Ken-cham."

119
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:27,490
He congratulated me
on becoming a kendama champion.

120
00:05:27,530 --> 00:05:28,460
Right.

121
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:31,230
I never imagined.

122
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:32,830
She's a real pro.

123
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:34,940
It's just a little hobby.

124
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:38,340
It's too bad I don't have one
with me now.

125
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:41,680
Wait, I think I might have one.

126
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:45,380
No, you don't. You don't have one.

127
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:49,820
Are you okay?

128
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:52,690
I'm just so nervous today.

129
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,460
I can't anymore.

130
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:58,190
Thanks, Nami.

131
00:05:58,230 --> 00:06:00,830
Sis totally bought it.

132
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:03,130
You think so?

133
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,570
What am I supposed to do now?

134
00:06:06,330 --> 00:06:10,270
I have to keep this act going
at work now too, right?

135
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,110
That's the problem.

136
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:17,880
I asked you to be my pretend
girlfriend because I liked you.

137
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:22,050
But you don't want your colleagues
to believe it, do you?

138
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:24,950
Because he liked me?

139
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:29,290
- No, I don't really mind...
- Look, so cute!

140
00:06:31,990 --> 00:06:36,660
Come to think of it, photographers
must know lots of pretty models.

141
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:39,800
So why did he choose me?

142
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:44,140
Even if it's pretend,
he must like me at least a little.

143
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:50,280
What if I really become
his girlfriend?

144
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:51,340
Um.

145
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:55,250
If you were my boyfriend...

146
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:58,320
I wouldn't really mind it that much.

147
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:02,690
Really? You mean it?

148
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,860
It's our little secret then.

149
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,100
Our little secret.

150
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:15,100
Right, okay.

151
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:19,840
Project "Keep My Boss Happy
as Her Brother's Fake Girlfriend."

152
00:07:20,370 --> 00:07:23,810
Great. So here's what we'll do.

153
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:30,020
First and foremost, stay away from her
as much as possible.

154
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:32,190
Never be alone with her.

155
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:33,150
What the...?

156
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:38,360
Prepare what you can beforehand.

157
00:07:38,630 --> 00:07:39,390
Good morning.

158
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:41,130
Like a ninja.

159
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:50,470
But make sure she sees hints of me
in your private life.

160
00:07:51,670 --> 00:07:53,040
- Sorry!
- Watch it.

161
00:07:53,070 --> 00:07:53,940
I'm sorry.

162
00:07:53,970 --> 00:07:54,740
What's this?

163
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:56,310
Your boyfriend?

164
00:07:56,340 --> 00:07:58,040
Let me see?

165
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:00,280
- Who?
- Give it back.

166
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:01,510
My boyfriend.

167
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:04,650
Who would have thought!

168
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:11,590
So far, it's a normal morning.

169
00:08:11,790 --> 00:08:13,290
Got it!

170
00:08:13,330 --> 00:08:15,330
Thanks, keep it up!

171
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:21,170
Here are the ones
you asked to borrow.

172
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:23,640
Thank you.

173
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:27,740
This is from our editor-in-chief.
Some sweets.

174
00:08:27,770 --> 00:08:29,110
I hope you enjoy them.

175
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,510
Thank you.

176
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:34,450
Ms. Suzuki.

177
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,650
- Running errands?
- Vice President.

178
00:08:38,150 --> 00:08:41,490
Yes, I have five more stops to make.

179
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:44,390
She's a real pusher.

180
00:08:44,420 --> 00:08:48,400
I'm sure you can learn a lot
working with her.

181
00:08:48,430 --> 00:08:50,700
It's not for me though.

182
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:54,870
I just want to do
an average, normal job.

183
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:56,300
Average?

184
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,840
Yes, average might be nice too.

185
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:06,210
Now, about whether or not
Cartier will buy the back cover ad.

186
00:09:06,210 --> 00:09:07,310
The back cover add
stands out and is most expensive

187
00:09:07,310 --> 00:09:10,780
They haven't answered back yet,
so it's not decided.

188
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,850
I'll let you know when they do.

189
00:09:13,290 --> 00:09:14,150
Cartier will...

190
00:09:14,190 --> 00:09:15,220
Do you know why?

191
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:19,260
Another magazine from our company
offended them before.

192
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:21,290
Things have been rocky since.

193
00:09:21,730 --> 00:09:25,200
On to our second feature,
the two-page culture section.

194
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:26,600
Any ideas?

195
00:09:27,030 --> 00:09:27,800
Yes.

196
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,970
How about a feature on sake?

197
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:34,510
Japanese cuisine
is trending worldwide.

198
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:37,840
So sake is becoming popular overseas.

199
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:44,080
No, no way.

200
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:48,090
We need something new,
something fresh, something striking.

201
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:50,420
A collaboration with a manga artist.

202
00:09:51,930 --> 00:09:54,560
Japan's manga is read worldwide.

203
00:09:55,430 --> 00:09:58,900
If we have manga illustrations
with fashion elements,

204
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:01,530
it could help with
the magazine's branding.

205
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:11,410
I like it.

206
00:10:12,010 --> 00:10:13,010
Yes!

207
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:14,810
Okay, who should it be?

208
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:17,520
Akira Toriyama, Takehiko Inoue...

209
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:18,650
Ukyo Arazome.

210
00:10:18,690 --> 00:10:19,820
Ukyo Arazome!

211
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,090
His works are known globally.

212
00:10:25,330 --> 00:10:27,660
We publish his manga,
so he knows us.

213
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:29,330
Let's do it.

214
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:32,330
Okay, Nakazawa and I
will go visit him shortly.

215
00:10:32,730 --> 00:10:35,240
- I'll write the proposal.
- Call the manga dept.

216
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:36,370
Mr. Handa.

217
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:40,270
Take her with you to the negotiation.

218
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:44,310
Suzuki?

219
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,250
- Huh?
- Wait.

220
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:50,420
She's just an attendant.

221
00:10:50,450 --> 00:10:51,650
Look.

222
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:52,920
Ukyo Arazome
Practicing new tricks

223
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:54,820
Kendama?

224
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:57,920
That girl is a kendama champion.

225
00:11:05,330 --> 00:11:07,470
I'll give you an average job.

226
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:12,010
Persuade the manga artist.

227
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:39,070
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

228
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,300
Wait a minute.

229
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:45,910
The puzzle on my desk
is a gift for a client.

230
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:47,440
Finish it by tomorrow.

231
00:11:47,470 --> 00:11:49,140
I can't negotiate.

232
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:53,010
I thought you loved to work
and wanted to work forever.

233
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:54,010
No, I...

234
00:11:54,050 --> 00:11:56,480
And since you're fluent,
translate this.

235
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,550
I can't!

236
00:11:58,990 --> 00:12:00,250
I can't negotiate.

237
00:12:00,290 --> 00:12:03,190
You're just the type
for a popular manga artist.

238
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:05,530
But I've never done it before.

239
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,630
Just go do kendama. That's it.

240
00:12:08,190 --> 00:12:09,400
Kendama?

241
00:12:09,430 --> 00:12:14,630
If all goes well, I'll talk to
my parents on your behalf.

242
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:19,470
But if it doesn't, you're fired.

243
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:22,910
You're firing me? No!

244
00:12:26,610 --> 00:12:29,350
Big trouble.
She's making me do the impossible!

245
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:31,780
I have to do kendama or I'm fired.

246
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:36,760
- Mr. Jun, let's all go for dinner...
- No thanks.

247
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:38,120
At least consider it.

248
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:41,790
We need a plan. I'll pick you up.

249
00:12:41,830 --> 00:12:42,600
Mr. Jun?

250
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:45,530
Mr. Nakazawa.

251
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:49,600
- Can't you go do the negotiation?
- Forget it.

252
00:12:51,140 --> 00:12:53,410
Here, limited sweet buns.

253
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,810
- Ms. Horai made me go buy them.
- No.

254
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:57,980
- It's good!
- No.

255
00:13:01,010 --> 00:13:02,950
What's Mr. Arazome like?

256
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:07,950
That was supposed to be my job.
Why would I help you?

257
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:09,460
Look it up yourself.

258
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:13,530
Yeah...

259
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:16,530
Look.

260
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,600
Have you read his manga?

261
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:21,670
No.

262
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:29,280
His most important work
is "Yobigami," 39 books long.

263
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:31,510
Wow, 39 books.

264
00:13:31,540 --> 00:13:34,880
Trust me, you won't be able
to put it down.

265
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:38,820
There's this great scene
in book three.

266
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:41,550
What?

267
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:43,560
You're a really great senpai.

268
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:44,960
Shut up.

269
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:50,130
- Nami!
- Junnosuke.

270
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,330
- Um...
- Her boyfriend.

271
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:03,780
My boyfriend.

272
00:14:05,810 --> 00:14:07,410
At least one thing above average.

273
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:11,350
Goodbye.

274
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:12,820
Nami.

275
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:16,490
I bought it. Let's practice.

276
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:19,930
Wow.

277
00:14:20,190 --> 00:14:21,960
A real "ken-cham."

278
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:24,960
Can you do it?

279
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:28,770
Go on, do it.

280
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,670
But don't break it.

281
00:14:33,340 --> 00:14:35,540
Just a big enough bruise.

282
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:37,210
How do I even do that?

283
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,150
Okay, fine. You can break it.

284
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:40,310
Really?

285
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:46,850
No, don't! This is impossible.

286
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:49,160
Look Nami.

287
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:59,100
You're cuter when you laugh.

288
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:06,340
I'll help. Let's do this together.

289
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:09,110
Okay.

290
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:19,190
Sorry for making you do that.

291
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:20,250
No probs.

292
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:21,950
I love puzzles.

293
00:15:26,930 --> 00:15:28,690
Ouch!

294
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:33,400
There you go.

295
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,670
That'll do.

296
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,680
- What?
- Nothing.

297
00:15:50,980 --> 00:15:51,750
What's this?

298
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:57,620
I'm having an exhibition
at a small gallery.

299
00:15:57,690 --> 00:15:59,390
I'm choosing what to put up.

300
00:15:59,430 --> 00:16:00,430
Coming in.

301
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:04,460
- This one's cute.
- This?

302
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:07,830
You should come.
I'll give you an invitation.

303
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,900
Sure.

304
00:16:12,070 --> 00:16:14,740
This is like...

305
00:16:14,770 --> 00:16:16,740
Like we're real lovers.

306
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,050
- Does it hurt?
- No.

307
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:22,010
All right, back to practice.

308
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:45,870
Nami.

309
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:03,920
Ow.

310
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,670
- Morning.
- Good morning.

311
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,170
Why am I...

312
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,070
You fell asleep practicing.

313
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:23,340
I tried to wake you up.

314
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:26,650
I still can't do it.

315
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:28,480
I'll make some coffee.

316
00:17:29,020 --> 00:17:30,220
Coffee!

317
00:17:32,180 --> 00:17:33,790
Is instant okay?

318
00:17:34,050 --> 00:17:34,990
No!

319
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:39,390
An all milk ristretto shot non-syrup
soy latte by 9 AM!

320
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,600
Thank you.

321
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,340
Hot!

322
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:10,920
Good morning, Ms. Horai.

323
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:14,030
You didn't go home last night?

324
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,230
Oh, no. This isn't...

325
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:18,100
It looks the same but it's not.

326
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,940
Excuse me. We scored an appointment
with Mr. Arazome.

327
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:25,200
1 PM today,
at Mr. Arazome's residence.

328
00:18:25,570 --> 00:18:26,710
Already?

329
00:18:28,410 --> 00:18:29,580
Bring me back good news.

330
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:31,110
Champion.

331
00:18:52,130 --> 00:18:54,370
What am I doing here?

332
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:59,070
Mr. Handa, about kendama...

333
00:18:59,110 --> 00:19:02,240
Sorry, but you won't be able
to show off your skills.

334
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:04,680
My smooth talk will win him over.

335
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:07,910
Oh good!

336
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:10,880
Is this your first negotiation?

337
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:13,020
- Yes.
- Well then.

338
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:17,160
I'll teach you the basics
about making a magazine.

339
00:19:18,220 --> 00:19:20,730
Our magazine targets women
in their 30s to 40s.

340
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:24,030
We take up fashion, beauty,
and culture.

341
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:27,270
A different person
is in charge of each.

342
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:30,870
Besides those pages
are the advertisements.

343
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:34,310
There are those created by
the clients themselves.

344
00:19:34,610 --> 00:19:38,810
And tie-ups where we create them
using their products.

345
00:19:41,810 --> 00:19:45,790
By the way, why was I chosen
as the odd jobs attendant?

346
00:19:46,590 --> 00:19:49,490
Because of what you wore
to the interview.

347
00:19:50,060 --> 00:19:50,960
What I wore?

348
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:54,690
When I saw your setup,

349
00:19:54,730 --> 00:19:57,700
I thought you might've even hired
a good stylist.

350
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:00,400
But then I saw your shoes.

351
00:20:00,430 --> 00:20:04,600
They were the tackiest things
I ever saw.

352
00:20:05,570 --> 00:20:08,810
A gift for you. For your new job.

353
00:20:11,110 --> 00:20:13,050
I haven't even gotten in yet.

354
00:20:16,780 --> 00:20:18,020
I don't need these.

355
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:23,320
People who love fashion
want to work in fashion.

356
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:27,190
And if they can't,
they get all gripey over the job.

357
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:30,100
They're too much to handle.

358
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:32,700
But you're not interested in fashion.

359
00:20:32,730 --> 00:20:34,570
That's why I chose you.

360
00:20:39,310 --> 00:20:40,970
I read your proposal.

361
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:44,380
I'm honored to be asked
by a fashion magazine.

362
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:46,150
- Then you'll do it?
- Well.

363
00:20:46,710 --> 00:20:50,720
I don't really see
why it has to be me.

364
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:54,350
I see.

365
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:58,190
There are many
world renowned manga artists.

366
00:20:58,620 --> 00:21:03,560
But your characters embrace the times
with their fashion.

367
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,960
And have a strong message.

368
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,930
Your latest book.

369
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,000
It was incredible.

370
00:21:10,540 --> 00:21:13,470
Where they reminisce about the past
as they fight.

371
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:16,080
"What am I doing here?"

372
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:18,910
A true tearjerker.

373
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:24,120
Nobody expresses feelings
like you can.

374
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:31,660
Nobody else. Only you.

375
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:33,830
I see.

376
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:41,600
By the way, I hear you like kendama.

377
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:46,640
Suzuki here is actually
a kendama champion.

378
00:21:48,370 --> 00:21:50,410
You said I wouldn't have to!

379
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:52,710
I'd love to see you do some tricks.

380
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:56,020
Oh please, it's really not much.

381
00:21:56,050 --> 00:21:56,880
Please, show me.

382
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:57,850
Go on.

383
00:21:57,880 --> 00:22:01,550
I would if I could,
but I don't have one with me now.

384
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:02,490
No problem.

385
00:22:08,530 --> 00:22:10,230
You can have this.

386
00:22:18,940 --> 00:22:20,210
That's incredible!

387
00:22:20,810 --> 00:22:22,340
Please, champion.

388
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:25,880
Thank you.

389
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,780
Come on.

390
00:22:32,850 --> 00:22:34,220
Do or die.

391
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:49,000
You want to be average?
Then take average responsibility.

392
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:53,010
Is it my responsibility?

393
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,370
That's not what I mean.

394
00:22:54,410 --> 00:22:56,680
Tools are all about how you use them.

395
00:22:56,710 --> 00:22:59,550
I missed you, Nami.

396
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,520
It was the worst.

397
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:13,060
Sorry to say, but you never should've
told her to go in the first place.

398
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:15,130
I'm sorry.

399
00:23:15,460 --> 00:23:17,500
Two pages in the first issue!

400
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:19,100
What will we do now?

401
00:23:19,530 --> 00:23:20,430
I'm sorry.

402
00:23:20,470 --> 00:23:21,970
Mr. Handa.

403
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:25,170
When you look for my new attendant,

404
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:27,070
make sure they're not a liar.

405
00:23:27,110 --> 00:23:28,640
Of course.

406
00:23:28,670 --> 00:23:29,540
Wait a minute!

407
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:32,510
Someone that doesn't lie
about being a champion!

408
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:38,280
Was it even my responsibility?

409
00:23:39,250 --> 00:23:40,090
Was it mine?

410
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:41,890
That's not what I'm saying.

411
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:45,820
Because look. I'm not even an editor.

412
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:49,330
She should've known
that was going to happen.

413
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:52,300
I knew it.

414
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:56,570
She did it on purpose
because I'm dating you.

415
00:23:57,570 --> 00:23:58,970
I don't think so.

416
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:01,170
It's always like that.

417
00:24:02,610 --> 00:24:06,410
I'm only ever chosen
for negative reasons.

418
00:24:07,650 --> 00:24:08,410
What do you mean?

419
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:12,450
I only got the job
because I wasn't fashionable.

420
00:24:13,090 --> 00:24:14,850
I don't get fashion either.

421
00:24:20,930 --> 00:24:23,600
Can I ask you a question?

422
00:24:28,270 --> 00:24:32,500
When you were looking for
a pretend girlfriend,

423
00:24:33,470 --> 00:24:34,940
why did you choose me?

424
00:24:38,380 --> 00:24:39,380
Well...

425
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:44,820
Because I'd never date you.

426
00:24:46,420 --> 00:24:49,820
I couldn't ask somebody
I might actually date to do this.

427
00:24:54,730 --> 00:24:56,330
Of course, yeah.

428
00:25:01,370 --> 00:25:02,940
See? I told you.

429
00:25:10,340 --> 00:25:11,240
I'm going home now.

430
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:12,540
Huh? Nami?

431
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,650
It's always like that.

432
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:22,760
I get all excited, but only on my own.

433
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:27,890
Really?
Then this is our little secret.

434
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:31,330
I knew it was pretend.

435
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,340
I knew it.

436
00:25:40,270 --> 00:25:42,670
I'll help. Let's do this together.

437
00:25:44,380 --> 00:25:45,980
It was all pretend.

438
00:25:46,850 --> 00:25:49,250
But I got all excited
and worked so hard.

439
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:52,650
I'm such an idiot.

440
00:26:00,030 --> 00:26:02,960
Where's the puzzle?
Reiko Horai

441
00:26:19,410 --> 00:26:20,680
What took you so long?

442
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:27,890
I thought I was fired.

443
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:29,890
I don't see your resignation paper.

444
00:26:33,030 --> 00:26:33,760
Um.

445
00:26:35,060 --> 00:26:37,260
I think you're responsible for it too.

446
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:39,530
For appointing you?

447
00:26:40,300 --> 00:26:42,840
- Yes.
- You don't get it, do you?

448
00:26:43,670 --> 00:26:49,140
You lied about being a champion
when you could do nothing.

449
00:26:49,540 --> 00:26:52,780
You think Mr. Arazome
would trust someone like that?

450
00:26:54,210 --> 00:26:57,380
That's his response
to your work ethic.

451
00:26:58,020 --> 00:26:59,950
So yes, it is your responsibility.

452
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:02,250
Not mine. End of story.

453
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:09,460
You say you want to be average.

454
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:12,700
But you just don't want to
put in the effort.

455
00:27:12,730 --> 00:27:14,530
You want to be average?

456
00:27:15,130 --> 00:27:16,970
Then take average responsibility.

457
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:36,090
I don't really think so.

458
00:29:07,380 --> 00:29:10,850
I'm extremely sorry
about the other day.

459
00:29:11,650 --> 00:29:13,650
It's all in the past now.

460
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:17,090
Um...

461
00:29:22,030 --> 00:29:23,960
Won't you let me show you a trick?

462
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:27,530
No need. I already know
how much you can do.

463
00:29:27,570 --> 00:29:29,030
Please, I beg you.

464
00:29:55,490 --> 00:29:56,600
I did it.

465
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:00,970
It's an easy trick, but...

466
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,170
Your wrist.

467
00:30:05,740 --> 00:30:07,410
You practiced a lot, huh?

468
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:12,740
I...

469
00:30:14,410 --> 00:30:16,180
This was a first for me.

470
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:18,980
Getting tasked with a real job.

471
00:30:20,690 --> 00:30:24,290
And working so hard
to achieve something.

472
00:30:26,590 --> 00:30:30,700
So I really regretted lying to you.

473
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:34,400
I understand.

474
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:37,500
One more thing.

475
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:40,940
"What am I doing here?"

476
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:48,480
When Akito lost to Toshiro
in book three,

477
00:30:48,510 --> 00:30:51,920
he trained so hard afterwards
and finally beat him.

478
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:56,460
Those words were a cry from the soul.

479
00:30:56,490 --> 00:30:59,420
I couldn't stop crying when I read it.

480
00:31:00,660 --> 00:31:03,300
The characters in your manga,

481
00:31:03,330 --> 00:31:06,570
even the minor ones
have a strong conviction.

482
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:11,240
How they'd risk their own lives
for their friends, it's so inspiring.

483
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:17,880
So, um...

484
00:31:20,110 --> 00:31:20,910
I...

485
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:25,580
I've become a fan of your work.

486
00:31:29,820 --> 00:31:31,460
I know it's too late.

487
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:37,360
But I just had to let you know.

488
00:31:41,430 --> 00:31:42,330
That's all.

489
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:45,070
Goodbye.

490
00:32:07,460 --> 00:32:08,230
Nami.

491
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:10,260
How did it go?

492
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:13,330
He understood.

493
00:32:13,930 --> 00:32:14,830
So he said yes?

494
00:32:14,870 --> 00:32:16,370
I couldn't ask him.

495
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:18,440
I see.

496
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:29,750
Look.

497
00:32:31,380 --> 00:32:33,150
I think we should end this.

498
00:32:34,390 --> 00:32:35,490
This pretend.

499
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:42,690
I've realized that
lying doesn't change reality.

500
00:32:44,500 --> 00:32:46,360
It'd just be running from it.

501
00:32:49,970 --> 00:32:50,940
Yeah.

502
00:32:53,740 --> 00:32:55,370
I'm gonna miss you.

503
00:32:56,740 --> 00:33:00,210
It was a fake relationship,
but the breakup feels real.

504
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:09,050
- I'll give this back.
- Keep it.

505
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:11,060
As a token of gratitude.

506
00:33:14,130 --> 00:33:15,430
Thank you.

507
00:33:16,630 --> 00:33:18,100
No, thank you.

508
00:33:21,030 --> 00:33:22,070
Stay well.

509
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:29,810
Oh yeah.

510
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:12,980
Junnosuke

511
00:34:14,090 --> 00:34:15,920
Lies don't become reality.

512
00:34:15,950 --> 00:34:19,490
Delete contact?

513
00:34:22,390 --> 00:34:25,400
About the French Embassy's party
this weekend.

514
00:34:25,430 --> 00:34:26,930
We've been invited.

515
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:31,700
Mr. Simon, Cartier's head of marketing
will be there too.

516
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:33,570
Thank you.

517
00:34:33,610 --> 00:34:36,040
And I'll go with you.

518
00:34:37,980 --> 00:34:39,840
- So you and me?
- Yes.

519
00:34:40,150 --> 00:34:41,080
Is that bad?

520
00:34:41,110 --> 00:34:42,710
No, of course not.

521
00:34:45,180 --> 00:34:46,320
Excuse me.

522
00:34:48,490 --> 00:34:49,720
Ms. Horai.

523
00:34:50,090 --> 00:34:51,160
A word please.

524
00:34:53,930 --> 00:34:56,330
Go ahead. I'll see you later.

525
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:58,330
- Please.
- Thank you.

526
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:06,840
I wanted to see you too. You go first.

527
00:35:08,570 --> 00:35:09,810
We broke up.

528
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:13,310
Junnosuke and I broke up.

529
00:35:14,450 --> 00:35:16,850
- So...
- And here's what I have to tell you.

530
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:20,520
I got a call from Mr. Arazome
five minutes ago.

531
00:35:20,550 --> 00:35:22,450
He agreed to our proposal.

532
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:28,830
He said it's for
his newest little fan.

533
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:31,760
Really?

534
00:35:32,960 --> 00:35:34,470
You really mean it?

535
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:38,000
Let me reward you.

536
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:40,470
I'm taking you to a party.

537
00:35:41,710 --> 00:35:42,770
A party?

538
00:35:50,980 --> 00:35:53,250
How have you been?

539
00:35:54,550 --> 00:35:54,920
Shinichi!

540
00:36:06,630 --> 00:36:09,170
Why, Reiko. Long time no see.

541
00:36:09,230 --> 00:36:10,400
Didn't expect you here.

542
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:12,140
Who might you be?

543
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:16,040
Haven't changed much, I see.

544
00:36:16,070 --> 00:36:20,880
Have you forgotten your former senpai
from living so long overseas?

545
00:36:21,610 --> 00:36:26,650
I'm the editor-in-chief for Zeal
right now.

546
00:36:27,150 --> 00:36:28,420
Here's my card.

547
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,120
You're kidding.

548
00:36:33,060 --> 00:36:35,560
Are you trying to get married
flashing your card?

549
00:36:35,590 --> 00:36:37,560
This isn't the place for that.

550
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,230
No, this isn't the place for you.

551
00:36:41,530 --> 00:36:45,940
I know you're here
to suck up to your clients.

552
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:52,180
What a tacky attendant. Former
editor-in-chief of Marie Claire?

553
00:36:52,680 --> 00:36:53,750
Look at you now.

554
00:36:56,210 --> 00:36:57,920
She's my competent assistant.

555
00:37:04,460 --> 00:37:05,560
Excuse me.

556
00:37:15,570 --> 00:37:16,600
Thank you.

557
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:25,340
- What...?
- Enjoying yourself?

558
00:37:28,610 --> 00:37:31,180
It's like a whole new world for me.

559
00:37:35,520 --> 00:37:36,520
Ms. Horai is next.

560
00:38:02,510 --> 00:38:04,020
Why does she have that?

561
00:38:19,260 --> 00:38:20,060
No way...

562
00:38:20,970 --> 00:38:22,830
- Suzuki, come here.
- No...

563
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:26,300
Go on, champion.

564
00:38:26,340 --> 00:38:28,040
No, I...

565
00:38:30,070 --> 00:38:32,080
I can't...

566
00:38:32,110 --> 00:38:35,780
That's Mr. Simon,
the head of marketing at Cartier.

567
00:38:35,810 --> 00:38:39,780
Cartier's advertisement is at stake.
I'm counting on you.

568
00:38:40,750 --> 00:38:42,690
That's why you brought me here?

569
00:38:50,730 --> 00:38:51,830
Ken-cham!

570
00:38:53,500 --> 00:38:58,300
Ken-cham, Ken-cham.

571
00:39:51,350 --> 00:39:53,420
That's enough.

572
00:39:53,930 --> 00:39:56,130
I didn't have time to prepare!

573
00:40:11,250 --> 00:40:12,510
What did you do?

574
00:40:13,380 --> 00:40:14,780
It's a long story.

575
00:40:16,650 --> 00:40:19,790
Hey, who sent the lemons
for the shoot here?

576
00:40:19,820 --> 00:40:20,860
Was it wrong?

577
00:40:21,820 --> 00:40:24,390
You again? Today's shoot is in Hiroo.

578
00:40:24,430 --> 00:40:25,360
Wake up.

579
00:40:26,030 --> 00:40:27,800
Sorry, I'll take it later.

580
00:40:28,300 --> 00:40:32,930
Mr. Arazome sent us the illustration.

581
00:40:32,970 --> 00:40:34,670
I want to see it!

582
00:40:38,010 --> 00:40:39,410
Wow!

583
00:40:40,710 --> 00:40:41,910
Want to see?

584
00:40:55,390 --> 00:40:57,290
Wait, it's Cartier.

585
00:40:57,320 --> 00:41:02,560
They came to us and said they wanted
to collaborate with Mr. Arazome.

586
00:41:03,130 --> 00:41:04,370
That's amazing!

587
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:08,170
And take a look at the back cover.

588
00:41:08,700 --> 00:41:10,900
They finally said yes?

589
00:41:10,940 --> 00:41:11,910
But how?

590
00:41:11,940 --> 00:41:13,610
Incredible.

591
00:41:17,080 --> 00:41:18,010
Is it...?

592
00:41:22,220 --> 00:41:24,550
Sir, have you seen Ms. Horai?

593
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:26,920
No.

594
00:41:27,290 --> 00:41:30,990
- Did you know about Cartier?
- Yes.

595
00:41:32,260 --> 00:41:33,990
Didn't Ms. Horai tell you?

596
00:41:34,330 --> 00:41:35,160
No.

597
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:41,440
She discovered that Mr. Simon
was a fan of Mr. Arazome's.

598
00:41:41,970 --> 00:41:43,600
Ukyo Arazome?

599
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:46,840
She asked me to set up
a chance to meet him.

600
00:41:47,610 --> 00:41:49,440
I'm taking you to a party.

601
00:41:50,010 --> 00:41:53,950
But the party wasn't
a business setting.

602
00:41:54,950 --> 00:41:57,850
So she needed a conversation starter.

603
00:41:59,220 --> 00:42:00,920
That's what the kendama was for?

604
00:42:01,460 --> 00:42:02,220
Yes.

605
00:42:03,060 --> 00:42:06,490
And it caught Mr. Simon's attention.

606
00:42:08,440 --> 00:42:09,330
Everyone,

607
00:42:10,230 --> 00:42:11,530
she's my assistant.

608
00:42:11,530 --> 00:42:12,500
You tried.

609
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:17,460
While it wasn't the most impressive
kendama performance,

610
00:42:18,450 --> 00:42:23,880
It is through kendama that
she's led us to successful negotiation.

611
00:42:24,350 --> 00:42:31,450
She has made it possible for this illustration
by manga artist, Mr. Ukyo Arazome,

612
00:42:32,080 --> 00:42:35,760
to be featured in the first
issue of our magazine.

613
00:42:36,860 --> 00:42:43,030
My assistant is still an incredibly
unexperienced new recruit.

614
00:42:44,300 --> 00:42:49,700
We're also incredibly new to
this fashion magazine industry.

615
00:42:50,540 --> 00:42:51,620
However,

616
00:42:51,790 --> 00:42:58,710
we'll venture into the global market
as a Japanese high-fashion magazine.

617
00:43:00,090 --> 00:43:02,320
We're embracing this challenge

618
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:07,330
in order to inspire the dreams of
people around the world.

619
00:43:10,150 --> 00:43:13,770
The name of our magazine is MIYAVI.

620
00:43:17,300 --> 00:43:20,400
So she sent me to negotiate
with Mr. Arazome.

621
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:23,200
And made me do kendama
at the party.

622
00:43:23,240 --> 00:43:24,570
All for that?

623
00:43:25,240 --> 00:43:28,780
Business is about
touching others' hearts.

624
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:34,050
You touched Mr. Arazome's heart.

625
00:43:34,750 --> 00:43:37,380
And Ms. Horai
touched Mr. Simon's heart.

626
00:43:37,890 --> 00:43:40,420
So I guess you could say,

627
00:43:40,450 --> 00:43:45,030
this success was a collaboration
between you and Ms. Horai.

628
00:43:47,490 --> 00:43:49,060
Good day.

629
00:43:51,670 --> 00:43:54,500
It's not bad being above average, huh?

630
00:44:05,180 --> 00:44:06,950
You used me.

631
00:44:06,980 --> 00:44:11,150
I just asked you a favor because
you're my brother's girlfriend.

632
00:44:15,390 --> 00:44:16,360
60 million yen.

633
00:44:17,620 --> 00:44:20,360
The advertisement
your kendama won us.

634
00:44:20,390 --> 00:44:21,660
Approximately 60 million.

635
00:44:23,060 --> 00:44:26,030
Even useless tools
are all about how you use them.

636
00:44:26,070 --> 00:44:27,730
And if they're still useless...

637
00:44:38,250 --> 00:44:42,620
I won't run away anymore
until I'm average!

638
00:45:19,420 --> 00:45:20,720
Junnosuke.

639
00:45:26,290 --> 00:45:28,430
Props for a shoot? Where to?

640
00:45:29,930 --> 00:45:31,030
It's okay.

641
00:45:32,170 --> 00:45:33,270
Your hand.

642
00:45:43,780 --> 00:45:45,250
Um, Junnosuke?

643
00:45:47,180 --> 00:45:49,220
Why are you here today?

644
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:54,560
I missed you, Nami.

645
00:45:57,890 --> 00:46:00,760
Before, I said it was because
I would never date you.

646
00:46:03,930 --> 00:46:07,300
But I realized there was
another reason I chose you.

647
00:46:09,170 --> 00:46:10,700
If it were you...

648
00:46:11,910 --> 00:46:14,840
I felt you'd really do your best
to help me out.

649
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:19,180
That I could believe in you.

650
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:25,390
That's why I chose you.

651
00:46:28,190 --> 00:46:29,490
Junnosuke.

652
00:46:35,830 --> 00:46:36,900
Here we are.

653
00:46:40,500 --> 00:46:41,700
Thank you.

654
00:46:46,710 --> 00:46:49,040
Bye, I guess.

655
00:47:05,660 --> 00:47:07,160
Do you like me?

656
00:47:15,500 --> 00:47:15,700
Either you quit or we quit.

657
00:47:15,700 --> 00:47:18,040
Next episode

658
00:47:18,040 --> 00:47:19,270
Interesting.

659
00:47:19,310 --> 00:47:21,070
Just ask, and they'll come back!

660
00:47:21,110 --> 00:47:23,110
Remember how much it costs
for me to beg?

661
00:47:23,140 --> 00:47:23,940
Stop the printing!

662
00:47:23,980 --> 00:47:25,250
We can't!

663
00:47:25,280 --> 00:47:26,050
Suzuki!

664
00:47:26,080 --> 00:47:27,350
- A mixer?
- Nami?

665
00:47:27,380 --> 00:47:30,150
I guess there's no way
I'm special.
